# Belt-and-suspenders. The allowlist Dockerfile is the load-bearing control
# (it COPYs explicit paths, never `.`), but this keeps the build context
# minimal and is a second line of defense against accidental disclosure.
#
# Three images build from this same root context:
#   - the static host (`Dockerfile`)        -> context/ issuer/ badges/ .well-known/ nginx/ README.md
#   - the on-demand render (`service/Dockerfile`) -> service/ generator/ badges/
#   - the OB3 issuer (`issuer-service/Dockerfile`) -> issuer-service/ context/
#     .well-known/ status/ generator/credentials.json tools/gen-did-json.ts
# so service/, generator/, issuer-service/ and the one tools/ file are
# re-included for those builds. All are public source; each Dockerfile still
# COPYs only its explicit paths. issuer-service/node_modules stays excluded —
# the image runs its own `npm ci` from the lockfile.
*
!context/
!context/**
!issuer/
!issuer/**
!badges/
!badges/**
!status/
!status/**
!.well-known/
!.well-known/**
!README.md
!nginx/
!nginx/**
!service/
!service/**
!generator/
!generator/**
!public/
!public/**
!issuer-service/
!issuer-service/**
issuer-service/node_modules
issuer-service/node_modules/**
!tools/gen-did-json.ts
